12/09/2003
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Deputy Interior Minister Boyko Kotsev announced on Thursday (11 September that Bulgaria broke up 30 human trafficking and document forgery rings last year.
In 2002, Kotsev said, the number of people attempting to cross the Bulgarian border illegally decreased by a half compared to the previous year.
He added that the number has dropped further this year.
In other news Thursday, the Netherlands praised Sofia's progress in EU accession talks.
A Bulgarian delegation is at The Hague this week, holding consultations with representatives of the Dutch government on the Justice and Home Affairs chapter of the accession talks.
(Dnevnik - 12/09/03;
BTA, BNT, BNR, bTV - 11/09/03)
